The paper discusses the use of predictive models and their potential for unintentional discrimination, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method for enabling interpretability of black-box models also involves data analysis and visualization, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the assessment of fairness in predictive models, which could also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
